BriefDescription: Counts the number of request that were not accepted into the L2Q because the L2Q is FULL.

Counts all L1D cacheline (dirty) evictions caused by miss, stores, and prefetches.  Does not count evictions or dirty writebacks caused by snoops.  Does not count a replacement unless a (dirty) line was written back.
Counts the number of cycles fetch stalls because of an icache miss. This is a cummulative count of cycles stalled for all icache misses.
Counts the number of instructions retired that were tagged because empty issue slots were seen before the uop due to icache miss
Counts the number of cache lines filled into the L2 cache that are in Exclusive state
Counts the number of cache lines filled into the L2 cache that are in Forward state
Counts the number of cache lines filled into the L2 cache that are in Invalid state
Counts the number of cache lines filled into the L2 cache that are in Modified state
Counts the number of cache lines filled into the L2 cache that are in Shared state
Counts the number of L2 cache lines that are evicted due to an L2 cache fill
Counts the number of L2 cache lines that are silently dropped due to an L2 cache fill
Counts the number of L2 cache lines that have been L2 hardware prefetched but not used by demand accesses

Counts the number of L2 prefetches initiated by either the L2 Stream or AMP that were  throttled due to Dynamic Prefetch Throttling. The throttle requestor/source could be from the uncore/SOC or the Dead Block Predictor.  Counts on a per core basis.
Counts the number of L2 prefetches initiated by the L2 Stream that were throttled due to Demand Throttle Prefetcher.  DTP Global Triggered with no Local Override. Counts on a per core basis.

Counts the number of L2 prefetches initiated by the L2 Stream and not throttled by DTP due to local override.  These prefetches may still be throttled due to another throttler mechanism besides DTP. Counts on a per core basis.

Counts the number of L2 prefetches initiated by either the L2 Stream or AMP that were throttled due to exceeding the XQ threshold set by either XQ_THRESOLD_DTP or XQ_THRESHOLD. Counts on a per core basis.

Counts the number of demand and prefetch transactions that the L2 XQ rejects due to a full or near full condition which likely indicates back pressure from the IDI link.  The XQ may reject transactions from the L2Q (non-cacheable requests), BBS (L2 misses
Counts the number of L2 Cache Accesses Counts the total number of L2 Cache Accesses - sum of hits, misses, rejects  front door requests for CRd/DRd/RFO/ItoM/L2 Prefetches only, per core event
Counts the number of L2 Cache Accesses that resulted in a Hit from a front door request only (does not include rejects or recycles), per core event
Counts the number of total L2 Cache Accesses that resulted in a Miss from a front door request only (does not include rejects or recycles), per core event
Counts the number of L2 Cache Accesses that miss the L2 and get BBL reject  short and long rejects (includes those counted in L2_reject_XQ.any), per core event

Counts the number of L2 Cache Accesses due to a snoop that can result in a hit or miss but not included in L2_request.hit or L2_request.miss (this only includes the first pass of the snoops, not the second pass read the data or change the state), per core event

Counts, on a per core basis, the total number of cacheable read-requests that Access  the Last Level Cache.  Read-requests include Dmd Loads/RFO/Ifetch (incl. L2/L1 HW prefetch).  LLC = L3 if L3 present, else L2.

Counts, on a per core basis, the total number of cacheable read-requests that Access (hits+misses) the Last Level Cache.  Read-requests include Dmd Loads/RFO/Ifetch (incl. L2/L1 HW prefetch).  LLC = L3 if L3 present, else L2.
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled to an icache or itlb miss which hit in the L2 cache
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to an icache or itlb miss which hit in the LLC, no snoop was required. LLC provided data

Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to an icache or itlb miss which hit in the LLC, a snoop was required, the snoop misses
or the snoop hits but no fwd. LLC provides the data
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to an icache or itlb miss which missed all the caches.  DRAM, MMIO or other LOCAL memory type provides the data

Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to an icache or itlb which missed all the caches, a snoop was required, and hits in other core or module on same die.  Another core provides the data with a fwd, no fwd, or hitM.

Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to an icache or itlb miss which missed all the local caches and memory, and hits in a remote memory.  Other NUMA cluster or other DIE provides the data
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled to an icache or itlb miss and the data was provided from an unknown source
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled to a demand load miss which hit in the L2 cache
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which hit in the LLC, no snoop was required. LLC provided data

Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which hit in the LLC, a snoop was required, the snoop misses
or the snoop hits but no fwd. LLC provides the data
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the caches.  DRAM, MMIO or other LOCAL memory type provides the data

Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the caches, a snoop was required, and hits in other core or module on same die.  Another core provides the data with a fwd, no fwd, or hitM.

Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled due to a demand load miss which missed all the local caches and memory, and hits in a remote memory.  Other NUMA cluster or other DIE provides the data
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled to a store buffer full condition
Counts the number of unhalted cycles when the core is stalled to a demand load miss and the data was provided from an unknown source
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss the L3 cache and hit in DRAM
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss the L3 cache and hit in Local HBM
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss the L3 cache and hit in Local PMM
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss the L3 cache and hit in a Remote DRAM
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss the L3 cache and hit in a Remote Cache and modified data was forwarded
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss the L3 cache and hit in a Remote Cache and non-modified data was forwarded
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss the L3 cache and hit in Remote HBM
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss the L3 cache and hit in Remote PMM
Counts the number of load ops retired that hit in the L3 cache in which a snoop was required and modified data was forwarded.
Counts the number of load ops retired that hit in the L3 cache in which a snoop was required and no data was forwarded.
Counts the number of load ops retired that hit in the L3 cache in which a snoop was required and non-modified data was forwarded.
Counts the number of load ops retired with a non-DRAM or MMIO source.
Counts the number of load ops retired that are uncacheable.
Counts the number of load ops retired with an unknown source.
Counts the number of load ops retired that hit the L1 data cache.
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss in the L1 data cache.
Counts the number of load ops retired that hit in the L2 cache.
Counts the number of load ops retired that miss in the L2 cache.
Counts the number of load ops retired that hit in the L3 cache in which no snoop was required.

Counts the number of load ops retired that hit in the L3 cache in which a snoop was required and it hit and forwarded data, it hit and did not forward data, or it hit and the forwarded data was modified.
Counts the number of load ops retired that hit in the L3 cache in which a snoop was required and it missed.
Counts the number of loads that hit in a write combining buffer (WCB), excluding the first load that caused the WCB to allocate.
Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked for any of the following reasons:  load buffer, store buffer or RSV full.
Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to a load buffer full condition.
Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to an RSV full condition.
Counts the number of cycles that uops are blocked due to a store buffer full condition.

Counts the number of issue slots every cycle that were not delivered by the frontend due to an icache miss
